    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n3105" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐν-αίσιμος</span></b> : <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">fateful,
            favorable</span> (opp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">παραίσιος</span>),
            <i><span class="en">Il. 2.353</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 2.182</span></i>, 159; then <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">proper, seemly, just</span>
            (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐν αἴσῃ, κατ᾽ αἶσαν, κατὰ μοῖραν</span>),
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀνήρ,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 6.521</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            φρένες,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 18.220</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            δῶμα</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 24.425</span></i>; neut.
          sing. as adv., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐναίσιμον ἐλθεῖν</span>,
          ‘opportunely,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 6.519</span></i>; predicative,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 2.122</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 7.299</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
